title: For Sale:  French Berthier Carbine in 8mm Lebel, with ammo, charger clip and sling
postcontent: This carbine is a real piece of history. It is the 5 shot verion of the earlier, 3 shot Berthier rifle, which was put into service in the 1890's. This piece was manufactured in the 1920's. It is loaded with a 5 shot N block clip that stays in the weapon. When the clip is empty, the user pushes a fresh clip into the weapon, which pushes the empty clip out of a trapdoor in the bottom of the rifle. It is chambered in 8mm Lebel, which is a rimmed cartridge. It was the first smokeless cartridge to be officially issued in any military service.  The front site has been removed and rewelded at some point, which is not uncommon in old surplus rifles, to increase accuracy.  Also included is 40 rounds of new, soft-point ammunition, a period correct leather sling and one charger clip. Everything you need to relive history. Buyer must be willing to sign paperwork stating that they are not a felon, barred from owning firearms, etc. I will need a driver's license number or CCW number.

title: For Sale:  AR-15 | AR-10 | AR's | AK's....
postcontent: Through corporate and military testing, the civilian AR15 was created to make it reliable, as well as as desirable of a weapon as it can be. These days, AR15’s aren’t just popular among Law Enforcement, yet many individuals seek to buy or build AR15's for their own individual use. Oftentimes, they’re called America's rifle.Read More About AR's and AK's HereThe AR15’s are available in a broad array of configurations, ranging from short carbine length models that have features like optical sights and adjustable length stocks, to heavy barrel models. The upper receivers integrate barrels of different lengths and weights, and handle various caliber ammunition, abound for this type of rifle. They’re easily installed, because of the rifle's modular design.Features and VariationsAutomatic and semi-automatic variants of the AR-15 are efficiently identical in look. Automatic variants possess a rotating selective fire button, permitting an operator to choose between 3 modes: semi-automatic, safe, and either 3 round burst or automatic, depending upon the model. Usually, civilian AR-15 models don’t have 3-round burst or automatic settings upon the fire selector.AR-15 Features:Direct impingement gas systemAircraft-grade aluminum receiverModular design permits for various accessories and will make repair simplerHigh velocity round, accurate, small caliberSynthetic grips and stock don’t splinter or warpFront sight is adjustable for elevationRear sight adjustable for elevation and windageBroad array of optical devices obtainable in addition to or as substitutions for iron sightsAK47 FeaturesAK47 became popular because of its multiple benefits which range from design, mass production, and size. The AK47s design is light, compact, and simple to maintain and clean because it was initially made for soldiers who wore gloves in cool winter to easily repair and operate. The AK47s average life span will range from 20 - 40 years depending upon usage and the weather conditions it was exposed to. With reliability will come a price of accuracy. AK47 was built for brief range engagement within mass infantry fire.
